  "sentiment": {
    "signal": "bearish",
    "headline": "Iran tensions and market fear combine to lift gold",
    "briefingBody": "Investor sentiment is deep in fear territory (Fear and Greed Index: 21), driven in part by Iran geopolitical tensions. Gold is responding as expected, rising as investors seek safety. The 10-year Treasury yield stands at 4.31%, with inflation running at 3.32% — giving a real rate of +0.32%, meaning monetary policy is mildly restrictive. The yield curve is positively sloped at +0.50, which does not yet signal a recession from rates. Until inflation falls closer to the Fed's 2% target, rate cuts remain unlikely, which supports the case for gold as an inflation hedge. Iran geopolitical risk is at 100/100. Any escalation would directly threaten oil supply, historically pushing energy prices up 15 to 30% and triggering a parallel rally in gold as a geopolitical hedge. Watch for a Fear and Greed recovery above 30 as the first signal that selling pressure may be exhausting, and for oil prices and gold for breakout moves on any confirmed geopolitical escalation.",
